                        <date>Late 17th - mid-18-century (?)</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; incipits and heading of the texts;
                           chapter titles and the words mǝʿrāf and kǝfl; numbers of the “tituli”;
                           elements of the punctuation signs and Ethiopic numerals; elements of the
                           quire marks and titles in the upper margin; parts of the Canon tables;
                           name of the owner.
 On fol. 21rb, the rubricated signs in the margin
                           between the columns are probably the quotation markers.
 Incipits of
                           each Gospel and Additio I are written alternately in red and black
                           lines.</seg>
